=== Supernatural Entities
The city is home to wandering and organized groups of all kinds of supernatural beings:

- *Blood Vampires*, feeding by sucking the blood out of their victim's neck. They can't stand the sun, and hide in nests during the day. Some are centuries old, mastering the blood magic from their inner beast and charming mortals to their will. Others are newborn, reckless, dangerous and so very very thirsty. Their body is effectively dead: no heartbeat, pale skin, dead eyes. It's not easy to notice at night, in the dark, unless you look closely. And even then, to the untrained eye they might just look sickly. They are supernaturally strong: and they get stronger as they ages, just like the body becomes less and less human. Some vampires have roamed the earth for millennia, but they are rare, even legends. Some say they look so monstrous that mortals will faint at first sight. When a blood vampire feeds, the victim is injected with a strong narcotic similar to heroin. The wounds on their neck close quickly and the victim is in a state of daze: they won't remember much, but they will be looking for more. Often they become blood dolls: servants to their vampire master, doing anything they ask to get another hit.
- *Ghouls* are created when a vampire makes a mortal drink their blood. They inherit some of the supernatural abilities of the vampire, for a time, as long as they regularly drink their blood. They are often loyal servants of their vampire master.
- *Soul Vampires*, dominating the dance floor, smooth talking at the bar counter, and surrounded by admirers, unwillingly feeding their souls to the beast. Whenever they stand, they are the center of the room, the life of the party. Some wander, trying to not feed on the same people too long so they don't start losing memories and going insane. Other revel in the attention and become politicians, cult leaders, celebrities, quickly gathering a large following: until they are found, forced to hide or worse. Their life is one of suffering and loneliness, their curse making anyone close to them go insane. They don't fear the sunlight, and they have magic in their blood: some say if you have a strong sense for magic, you can see their skin sparkle when exposed to direct sunlight. Their condition is hereditary, but they live for centuries: the family is large, but pure blooded soul vampires are rare, and extremely dangerous. The ancient, pure blooded ones control the entertainment industry throughout the world from the shadows.
- *Werewolves* are a species similar to humans, with magical elements in their body allowing them to be in tune with nature and transform into large wolves. Mature werewolves are able to remember and even control their behavior when transformed by the energy of the full moon, but young ones are reckless, mindless beasts of the night. Full blooded Werewolves are able to spontaneously turn into wolves even without the full moon. For most of them though, they have only some Werewolf blood in them and need a ritual beneath the full moon in order to turn.
- *Wizards and Witches* are humans that inherited a magical affinity from their parents. This affinity can emerge as spontaneous magical abilities with varying type and strength. With training and mentorship, it can be developed into true, sometimes earth shattering power. But it is not without risk: magic can bend and shape the body, mind and soul of those who wield it.
- *Faith* can be deadly against supernatural and magical beings. True faith, inbued into artifacts and wielded by the faithful, is an extremely powerful form of magic.
- *Artifacts*: it's not just creatures that hold supernatural power in this world. Artifacts can do that as well, by being inbued with the Faith of mortals or by being shaped by the expert hands of powerful mages. Some of these items are in the hands of various organizations of the underworld, but some remain hidden. Until someone unearths them.

=== Mortals

Mortal is the term used in the underworld to refer to humans that have no magical or supernatural abilities. They are the regular people, they live in the background of stories in this world. Except when a loved one goes missing. Or when a thirsty Vampire is in the right place at the right time. Or when something big happens in the middle of the street, the sirens are racing in, the horrified screams of the witnesses fill the damp air. Somewhere, a phone dings. The FSB agent picks it up, and gets moving.

Either way, most people will deny the supernatural even when presented with evidence. They will say it's fabricated, they will point out AI generated pictures. When cellphones with cameras became popular, the underworld reeled, but now photographic evidence is not a big deal anymore.

