=== Magic

There are many forms and schools of magic, but most of them are studied and developed by the Wizardry Union. Magic is innate, and requires predisposition for being used. But some are late bloomers: magical awakening can happen at any age and at varying levels. Magic affinity can be developed (assuming it is not totally absent) but people starting with the strongest awakening have the highest potential, both for greatness and for peril.

No magic is free to use, there is always a cost to pay: most commonly energy is drawn from one's soul or the surroundings, artifacts of power, or natural sources such as the Moon, Fire, Water, Earth, Wind. Dark and dangerous forms of magic such as Blood Magic can have serious consequences to their users, shaping them as much as they shape the magic.
=== Folklore and Mythology

Everyone knows monsters aren't real. Those videos on the internet? Fake, CGI, AI generated. The vampire forums online? Roleplay. The rituals on those books? Fiction. That unexplained phenomena? Just something science cannot explain yet, or some trick or illusion.

The initiated will know that monsters and magic are real, but it is very difficult to turn a "normal" mortal into a believer: think about yourself, would you believe this stuff is real? What would it take for you to believe?
